# Cursor browser policy (mandatory)

## Default: native Browser Tab

Use the **Browser Tab** pane beside chat (user's logged-in session). Do **not** open external Chrome or call `plugin-playwright-playwright` tools unless both conditions below are met.

## External browser (Playwright) â€” only when explicitly requested

Use **external Playwright Chrome** (`plugin-playwright-playwright-*`) **only if**:

1. The user **explicitly asks** for external browser / Playwright / separate Chrome window, **and**
2. The user has turned **ON** the Playwright plugin: **Cursor Settings â†’ Tools & MCP â†’ Plugin MCP Servers â†’ playwright**.

If the user did not ask for external browser, or Playwright plugin is OFF â†’ use native Browser Tab only.

## Conflict warning

When **both** Browser Tab and Playwright plugin are ON, Playwright often hijacks browser calls to external Chrome (`about:blank` or Login). If that happens while the user wanted the native tab, tell them to run `tools/fix_cursor_native_browser_state.ps1` (Cursor closed) and disable third-party skills import + Playwright MCP.

## Known blockers (this machine)

- `composerState.yoloMcpToolsDisabled: true` â€” MCP tools disabled in Auto-Run; patch via `fix_cursor_native_browser_state.ps1`
- `composerState.playwrightProtection: true` â€” same script sets false
- Third-party skills import ON â€” imports `~/.codex/skills/playwright/SKILL.md` (CLI skill; separate from MCP but confuses UI)
- Agent logs route `browser_*` to `providerIdentifier=playwright` not native Browser MCP provider

## Agent behavior (native tab â€” default)

- **Do not call** any `plugin-playwright-playwright-*` tool (including `browser_tabs`, `browser_snapshot`, `browser_navigate`) unless the user explicitly asked for external Playwright **and** the plugin is ON. Those calls can spawn external Chrome even when the user wants the native tab.
- If only Playwright tools exist and Playwright is OFF, tell the user native browser tools are not wired to this chat â€” do **not** try browser MCP calls.
- When native tools are available and Playwright is off: first `browser_tabs` list, then snapshot on the existing tab only if tools are not Playwright-prefixed.

## Verification before browser work

`browser_tabs` (list only). Success = current tab matches what the user sees. Failure = ask user to reset Browser Automation (see `docs/ops/CURSOR_NATIVE_BROWSER.md`).

